parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, it can cause damage to the engine and other components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine oil level is low or empty
the oil light does not come on
the engine stalls or hesitates
the engine makes a loud noise or tapping sound
the vehicle shakes or vibrates
and the exhaust is dirty or black.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag indicator can cause the airbag to be disabled, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag indicator light turns on and off intermittently
the airbag light comes on when a passenger is in the seat
the airbag light goes off when the passenger buckles their seatbelt
the airbag light stays on even when there is no passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag light comes on after a crash
the vehicle is damaged but the airbag does not deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unnecessarily or not deploy at all, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag warning message appears on the dashboard
the airbag system is malfunctioning
the airbag sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
warning lights on the instrument panel remain illuminated
the brakes make an abnormal noise
the gearshift is stuck
the vehicle won't start
the battery drains
and the radio and dashboard lights malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle hesitates or stalls while shifting gears
and the transmission control module malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery and charging system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery drains
the vehicle won't start
the battery needs to be replaced frequently
and the charging system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warning Lights and Instrument Panel Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the warning lights and instrument panel can cause the driver to be unaware of potential safety issues, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The warning lights on the instrument panel remain illuminated
the traction and low voltage lights need to be replaced
and the dashboard lights malfunction.
